history.content:
This summer, I've been trying to enroll in CS 162.  I enrolled phase 1 while declaring my CS double, so at that point I was only a math major.  I had declared CS the week before the purge, but I was kicked off the waitlist anyways.  I was annoyed, but I just re-added myself, and I was position 17 on the waitlist for a long time.  However, now that they filled the class to capacity off the waitlist, I'm still waitlisted as position 14, as if I still hadn't declared CS.  Can someone tell me why I'm still not officially enrolled in CS 162, and what I can do about it?

Also the section I selected still has 9 empty seats, so I doubt that's the issue.
history.subject: CS 162 enrollment issues
